        <p>
-Renowned for its diverse wildlife, especially large mammals.
</p>
<p>
-Home to lions, cheetahs, hippos, buffalos, wildebeests, elephants, zebras, giraffes, and rhinos.
</p>
<p>
-Diverse bird population, including flamingos and ostriches.
</p>
<p>
-National parks and reserves are habitats for these animals.
</p>
<h3>
    2. Exploration of Parks Nyeri County:
</h3>

<div class="home-button">
    <a href="https://www.tripadvisor.com/Attractions-g616012-Activities-c57-Nyeri_Central_Province.html"
    >Click to See Parks</a>  
     </div>
<p>
-Located between Aberdare and Mt. Kenya National Parks.
</p>
<p>
-Rich in wildlife.
</p>
<p>
-Highest forest cover in the country.
</p>
<p>
-Forests are home to elephants, leopards, black rhinos, buffalos, colobus monkeys, warthogs, bushbucks, spotted hyenas, and olive baboons.
</p>
<p>
-Forests act as critical water catchments.
     </p>
